\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. A. collina} Ten.,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Nap.} xxxix (1811) ({\i A. muralis} Bertol., {\i A. rosea} DC.). Perennial 10-30 cm, pale green, often branched; stem pubescent below, glabrous above or with tri- to 6-fid, stalked hairs. Basal leaves attenuate-petiolate, obovate, obtusely and deeply dentate, rounded at the apex, with branched hairs (sometimes setose on the margin); cauline leaves 6-14, rounded at the base, oblong to ovate, the uppermost lanceolate, scarcely broader than the stem. Flowers 8-18; petals 6-10 × 2-4 mm, erect, cuneate to spathulate, white to pink or purplish. Infructescence strict; siliqua 30-90 × 1·2-2·2 mm; pedicels 4-12 mm, valves with an indistinct median vein; style 0·5-2 mm. 2n = 16.{\i  • S. & S.C. Europe.} Al Bl Bu Co Ga Gr He Hs It Ju Sa Si [Be].
