\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. A. recta} Vill.,{\i  Hist. Pl. Dauph. }{\b 3}: 319 (1788) ({\i A. auriculata }sensu DC., non Lam.). Annual 10-30 cm; stem simple or branched above; pubescent, the hairs 2- to 5-fid. Basal leaves petiolate, ovate or obovate, entire; cauline leaves 5-14, 6-20 mm, sessile, auriculate, ovate to oblong, rounded at the apex. Flowers 7-40; pedicels up to 5 mm at anthesis; petals 2-3·5 mm, white. Infructescence lax, flexuous; siliqua 10-35 × 0·6-1 mm, glabrous to puberulent, patent; pedicels 2-5 mm; style up to 0·5 mm. Seeds up to 1 mm, unwinged, brown. {\i Europe, except the north and many of the islands.} Al Au Bu Cr Cz Ga Ge Gr He Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs(B, C, W, K, E) Sa Si [Be].
